cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a neural architecture for predictive processing in the sensorimotor system, which involves hierarchical encoding of regularities between perception and action. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for the proposed neural architecture, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) for the use of the PredNet Network, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the embodied learning process and predictive processing, cs.RO (Robotics) for the mobile robot experiment, and cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the use of the multi-layer perceptron network. Among these, cs.NE is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the neural architecture and its hierarchical encoding of regularities.
